JS components can all be used without writing a single line of javascript code:
- data-* attributes(e.g. data-toggle,data-spy)


JQuery
Lightweight javascript library
Feature-rich:
-HTML/DOM manupilation
-CSS manupilation
-HTML event methods
-effects and animations
-AJAX

Jquery Syntax
- it's syntax starts with a dollar sign which means that it acceses JQuey's library plugins that are avilable.
	
$(selector).action()

	-$: define/access JQuery
	-(selector): to query and find HTML elements
	-action(): action to be performed on the element(s)
	-e.g.,$("p").hide(),$(#mycarousel").carousel('pause')

	e.g.
	/*
		here the selector document specify the whole document, ready is the action, i.e, when the selector is ready intialise the function.
		In the entire document whoever meets the 2nd selector criteria, i.e., data-toggle="tooltip" will be manupilated using the javascript function tooltip()
	*/
	<script>
		$(document).ready(function(){
			$('[data-toggle="tooltip"]').tooltip();
		});
	</script>


JQuery Selectors
Ways of specifing the selectors
-Any HTML element e.g, "p", "button" etc. the element us placed inside a tag and this way it means all the specified element in the document must be selected. 
-Using ID. eg. #nycarousel.
-By classes, eg., ".btn",".btn.btn-default"			//here second example means, elements which have both the classes applied btn and                                                   btn-default are to be selected.
-By attributes using square bracket, e.g., "[href]"
-Current element: $(this) // it specifies that the already selected elements

JQuery Events
-MOUSE
-KYBOARD
-FORM - submit, change, focus, blur
-DOCUMENT, WINDOW - load, resize, scroll, unload